## 💡 Common Patterns to Enforce

### Pattern 1: API Endpoint Structure
**Reference**: ai/skills/api-development.md Section 1

```javascript
const endpoint = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    // 1. Validate
    const { field } = req.body;
    if (!field) return res.status(400).json({ message: "Required" });
    
    // 2. Authorize
    if (req.user.id !== resource.userId) {
      return res.status(403).json({ message: "Forbidden" });
    }
    
    // 3. Business logic
    const result = await Model.findByIdAndUpdate(...);
    
    // 4. Response
    return res.status(200).json({ message: "Success", data: result });
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(500).json({ message: "Error", error: error.message });
  }
};
```

### Pattern 2: Database Query Optimization
**Reference**: ai/skills/database-optimization.md Section 2

```javascript
// ✅ Use .populate() with field selection + .lean()
const orders = await Order.find({ seller: id })
  .populate("buyer", "name email -password")
  .lean()
  .limit(100);
```

### Pattern 3: Payment Webhook Verification
**Reference**: ai/agents/security.agent.md Section 3

```javascript
// ✅ ALWAYS verify signature first
const signature = req.headers["x-razorpay-signature"];
const verified = crypto
  .createHmac("sha256", SECRET)
  .update(req.rawBody)
  .digest("hex") === signature;

if (!verified) return res.status(401).json({ message: "Unauthorized" });
```

